This PR/issue depends on:
* leanprover-community/mathlib4#9935
By **[Dependent Issues](https://github.com/z0al/dependent-issues)** (🤖). Happy coding!
<!-- By Dependent Issues (Action) - DO NOT REMOVE -->

Here are some general remarks:
* Try to follow the mathlib coding style (which is not as strict as it used to be, but there are some guidelines https://leanprover-community.github.io/contribute/style.html and we try to have a certain uniformity in the code presentation).
* As the notion of homotopy that we shall soon define for simplicial objects (or at least simplicial sets) shall be slightly different from this one, I believe that this file should be renamed `AlgebraicTopology.QuasiCategory.Homotopy`. As `Quasicategory` is defined as `SSet.Quasicategory`, I would think that the whole file should be under the namespace `SSet.Quasicategory` instead of `Quasicategory`.
* As simplicial sets are particular cases of simplicial objects, we can take advantage of the dot notation, so that `(C.map (δ 2).op) τ` can be rephrased as `C.δ 2 τ`, etc.
* In the introduction of the file, try to include a reference paper/book where the mathematical notions appear, so that users of mathlib can get easier access to the mathematical background.
* In general, we should not mark as `awaiting-review` PRs which depend on other PRs.

There are ways to take more advantage of the Lean type theory in order to get a better design of homotopies (and this would be consistent with the design of homotopies between morphisms of homological complexes), something like:
```lean
universe u

variable {C : SSet.{u}} [Quasicategory C]

structure Homotopy (f g : C _[1]) where
  τ : C _[2]
  δ₂ : C.δ 2 τ = f
  δ₁ : C.δ 1 τ = g
  δ₀ : C.δ 0 τ = C.σ 0 (C.δ 0 f)

def Homotopic (f g : C _[1]) : Prop := Nonempty (Homotopy f g)
```
Then, you may introduce a definition `Homotopy.refl`, and lemmas `Homotopic.refl/symm/trans`.
